Cut the @Tenderstem® Broccoli{80%g} into thirds.

Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g} and @Water for the Sauce{100%ml}. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the @Butter{30%g} until melted. Simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, boil a full #kettle{}.

Pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

Add the @Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta{250%g} and broccoli. Cook until tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Drizzle with @oil{} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has thickened, stir in the @Creme Fraiche{75%g} and cook for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Halve the @Ciabatta{1}.

Toast the ciabatta halves in your #toaster{} until golden.

Once toasted, drizzle some @olive oil{}.

Once the sauce has thickened, add the cooked pasta, broccoli and @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} to the pan.

Gently stir to melt the cheese and combine everything together.

Share your creamy garlic butter pasta between your #serving plates{}.

Serve with your toasted ciabatta alongside. Enjoy!